works perfect. For those not familiar with installing programs with added patches do this. Download the file obviously first. Do the set up install, as a free trial version. uncheck the stupid add ons for toolbars and homepages. Once the install is completed. Go to your task tray on the bottom right corner and right click on the programs icon. Click exit, then go to the dap folder and open it. You will find it under program files. Then open the patch folder and copy the exe. file located in it. in the other window where you have opened the dap folder under program files right click and paste into the folder when it asks if you wish to replace file with new file hit yes. and then double click the new exe file you pasted in there. There you go , you now have premium Dap you can verify this by right clicking on the icon in the task tray and you will notice there is no upgrade to premium option in there anymore. THis process is pretty standard for any program+ patch you will find on here. Hope this helps to the newer users.
